   "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Both are premium wired-RF systems and both are excellent. Lutron RA2 Select / RadioRA is the more recognised global brand with strong reliability and a wide range of compatible drivers. Rako is the UK favourite, designed and supported in Britain, with arguably better integration with non-Lutron mains-dimmable LED drivers. For a typical Somerset home we usually recommend Rako on the basis of price and local support, but specify Lutron where the client already has Lutron elsewhere or wants the very widest third-party compatibility."}},
  {"@type": "Question", "name": "Hue bulbs vs smart switches — what's the difference?",
   "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Hue bulbs are the easy retrofit: change the bulb, install the bridge, done. The catch is you must leave the wall switch always on, otherwise the bulbs lose power and the smart features stop working. Smart switches (Lightwave RF, Lutron, Rako, Shelly behind a normal switch) replace or sit behind the existing wall switch — so the wall switch still works exactly as before AND can be controlled remotely. Smart switches are the more elegant solution but require an electrician; smart bulbs are DIY-friendly but limit you to one circuit."}},
  {"@type": "Question", "name": "Do I need new wiring for a smart home?",
   "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Usually no, especially with wireless RF systems (Hue, Lightwave RF, Aqara, Rako wireless). For wired Lutron RA2 or wired Rako with dedicated controllers and dimmer modules in the consumer unit, additional cabling is sometimes needed but we can often retrofit using existing switch drops. We assess this on the site survey. Most retrofits can be done without lifting floors."}},
  {"@type": "Question", "name": "Will it work with Alexa, Google or Siri?",
