  {"@type": "Question", "name": "What is a neutral wire and why does it matter for smart switches?",
   "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "A neutral is the return wire that completes a lighting circuit. Older UK homes commonly only have line and switched-line at the wall switch, with no neutral pulled to the switch position. Most modern smart switches need a neutral to power their internal radio. We check this during the survey — where there's no neutral, we either pull one in (best), use a neutral-free smart switch (Lutron Caseta, certain Shelly modules, Lightwave with capacitor), or fit a smart relay behind the switch backbox instead."}},
