  <h2 class="section-heading">Premium vs Entry &mdash;<br>What's the Difference?</h2>
  <p class="section-desc" style="max-width:720px">Both work. They sit at different price points and serve different needs. Here is the honest version.</p>

  <div class="tier-grid">
   <div class="tier-card premium">
    <span class="tag">Premium &mdash; Wired RF</span>
    <h3>Lutron RA2 + Rako</h3>
    <p>Dedicated controller in the consumer unit (or nearby), purpose-made dimmer modules wired into each lighting circuit, scene keypads on the wall. Local control runs on the system's own RF or wired backbone &mdash; works perfectly when the Wi-Fi is down.</p>
    <ul>
     <li>Best for new builds, full refurbs, listed-property restorations</li>
     <li>Recall whole-house scenes from a single keypad press</li>
     <li>Excellent dimming &mdash; no flicker, no buzz, no dropouts</li>
     <li>Local fallback &mdash; lights still work if router dies</li>
     <li>Higher upfront cost; lasts 15+ years</li>
    </ul>
   </div>

   <div class="tier-card standard">
    <span class="tag">Good &mdash; Wireless Retrofit</span>
    <h3>Hue + Lightwave RF + Aqara</h3>
    <p>Wi-Fi or Zigbee bridges, smart bulbs or smart switches, retrofitted into existing fittings. No new wiring needed. Excellent value for renters, smaller homes, or rooms you want to upgrade one at a time.</p>
    <ul>
     <li>Best for retrofits, rentals, room-by-room upgrades</li>
     <li>App and voice control via Alexa / Google / HomeKit</li>
     <li>Mix-and-match across rooms as budget allows</li>
     <li>Most features depend on a working internet connection</li>
     <li>Lower upfront cost; replace bulbs every 3-5 years</li>
    </ul>
   </div>
  </div>
